					<p>
The Norman E. Borlaug International Science and Technology Fellows Program offers short-term training and collaborative researchopportunities in international agricultural science and policy through exchanges for entrylevel scientists, faculty, policymakers and regulators from developing and middle-income countries. Although open to participants from developing or middle-income countries worldwide, the Program gives priority to Fellows from Africa, Latin America and the Caribbean, and Asia.</p>
